  "body": "### Description of the Issue\r\n\r\nSometimes when entering the value on send transaction, after entering it, it will be reset to zero. This only happens once, after you fix the set to zero, it won't happen again.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nThis has been inconsistent, but:\r\n\r\n1. Unlock a wallet on send\r\n2. Set the address\r\n3. Set the value to `1`\r\n4. Unfocus the field\r\n5. Value is set back to `0`\r\n\r\n### Console Logs / Screenshots\r\n\r\n#### Setting to 1 action\r\n\r\n<img width=\"938\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-02-28 at 3 18 21 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/649992/36811175-e44ba19c-1c9a-11e8-801b-d0e63c9e4686.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Followed soon after by being set to 0 action (That I didn't trigger)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"912\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-02-28 at 3 18 27 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/649992/36811188-ecf65760-1c9a-11e8-9aad-04dd5ddd09d8.png\">\r\n",
